## How I work with enterprise teams

I operate as an embedded consultant. That means I do not hand over a PDF and disappear. I work alongside your developers, product managers, content strategists, and marketing leads as a specialist resource within your existing workflows.

In practice, this looks like:

- **With engineering:** Prioritised technical tickets written in their language, with clear acceptance criteria and implementation guidance. I join sprint planning where needed and review deployments for SEO impact.
- **With product:** Ensuring new features, URL structures, and user journeys are search-friendly from the design phase — not retrofitted after launch.
- **With content:** Keyword strategy, content briefs, cannibalisation audits, and editorial calendars aligned to search demand and commercial priority.
- **With leadership:** Monthly reporting that connects SEO activity to commercial outcomes — revenue, pipeline, market share — not just rankings and traffic.

This model works because enterprise SEO fails when it is siloed. The consultant who only talks to the marketing team will never get engineering to implement their recommendations. I bridge that gap.

If you are exploring broader [SEO consulting](/services/seo-consulting/) options or comparing approaches, I am happy to discuss how an embedded model compares to agency retainers or in-house hires.

## Industries I work with

I have delivered enterprise SEO programmes across several sectors, each with distinct challenges.

**Financial services.** Regulatory constraints on content, strict compliance review processes, and YMYL scrutiny from Google. SEO here requires patience, precision, and close collaboration with legal teams.

**Retail and ecommerce.** Product catalogue management, faceted navigation, seasonal inventory changes, and marketplace competition. The technical challenges are immense, but the commercial upside is direct and measurable.

**SaaS and technology.** Product-led growth, documentation sites, programmatic landing pages, and competitive content marketing in crowded verticals. Speed of iteration matters here.

**Publishing and media.** Content volume, news SEO, paywalled content handling, and Core Web Vitals across ad-heavy page templates. Crawl budget and indexing efficiency are constant priorities.

**Travel and hospitality.** Location-based pages at scale, multi-language content, user-generated reviews, and intense competition from aggregators. Structured data and local search integration are critical.

## Pricing

Enterprise SEO consulting is not a fixed-price product. The scope, complexity, and duration vary significantly between organisations. A mid-sized SaaS company with 10,000 pages and a single domain has different needs to a multinational retailer with 2 million URLs across 15 markets.

I typically work on retained engagements of three to twelve months, with pricing based on scope and time commitment. For a detailed breakdown of how SEO consulting fees work, see my guide on [how much does SEO cost](/services/how-much-does-seo-cost/).

The best starting point is a conversation. I will ask about your current SEO maturity, your team structure, your technical stack, and your commercial objectives — then propose a scope and fee that matches.

